						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold and a lamp-stand placed with the <hi rend="italic">patipādamūlattār</hi> of the temple of Mahādēva at Tiruchchōṟṟuttuṟai a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> in Kiḻār-kūṟṟam for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple, by <hi rend="bold">Nambaṉ-Kāṇḍaṉ</hi> servant <hi rend="bold">of Marudaṉ-Baṭṭaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Śōḻavēḷāṉ</hi> the headman of Karugāvūr in Āvūr-kūṟṟam (mentioned in No. 173 above).</p>						

						</summary>
